{
  "text": "All embryos were scored using established morphological criteria and cell number [CITATION_1] . Embryos were then incubated in 4 ml drops of a defined culture medium with a composition based on that of human tubal fluid [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] under washed, equilibrated paraffin oil (Medicult UK Ltd), at 378C, and 5% CO 2 in air. After 24 h of culture, embryos were scored and were then either continued in culture in a fresh drop of medium up to the blastocyst stage or fixed and prepared for chromosome analysis. All drops of spent culture media were immediately frozen at 2808C until amino acid analysis.",
  "correct_citation": {
